Invocations of templates where the first parameter is a language code, but it does not match the language header.

The three Norwegian lects (nb, nn, no) are treated as identical.

Excluded for now:
* Anything involving Chinese (zh), either as the L2 header or the language code.
** It throws up too many false positives (zh <-> cmn and the like).
* All instances of {{tl|syn}} under a Dutch L2 header.
** Someone has incorrectly used this template to include hundreds of translations of Dutch toponyms into regional Dutch languages – Limburgish (li), Zealandic (zea) and Dutch Low Saxon (nds-nl). Example: {{m|nl|Loppersum}}. I've suppressed these in the list for the time being.
Last updated 2023-01-01.
==#-A==
